{"type":"message","id":"5cd7647f","parentId":"f6284b1e","timestamp":"2026-04-15T04:47:49.280Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me compare the current state vs the last known state:\n\n**Last known state (04:44 UTC):**\n- Active: \n  1. agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7 (5p progress cron)\n  2. agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31 (DTLX 5p)\n  3. agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e (Agent Status to Lead)\n  4. agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134 (Lead direct)\n- Idle: telegram:group:-5163901258\n\n**Current state (04:47 UTC):**\n- Active (status=running):\n  1. agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7 ✅ still running\n  2. agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31 ✅ still running\n  3. agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e ✅ still running (was running, now shows running but was aborted)\n\nWait, let me reconsider. The Telegram direct session ended and transitioned to done status, which is a change from the previous state where it was active.\n\nThe group session also changed from idle to running. And the main session disappeared entirely—it was in the idle list before but now it's gone from the sessions_list response.\n\nLooking at the state changes: the direct session died and the group session became active, plus the main session vanished. That's three significant changes since 04:44 UTC. I should flag these for the report. Also noticing the Telegram direct session ended at 04:44. Let me re-examine the current sessions more carefully—the cron:ed2d0b5d session is still running and appears to be the one executing right now, while cron:6f3323ef is also active, and there's another one starting up as well.\n\nLooking at the full session list now, I'm seeing a mix of active cron jobs, completed Telegram sessions, and a few other entries that don't seem to fit the pattern.\n\nComparing this to the last recorded state from 04:44, I can see a couple of significant changes: the telegram direct session that was active then has now finished, and the main session that was idle appears to be gone entirely. The three cron jobs remain consistent across both snapshots. I'm getting confused about the timing here—the direct session actually ended at 04:44 based on the previous cycle's note, but the heartbeat state shows it was still active at that time. Let me trace through the sequence: the heartbeat ran at 04:44 and logged the state showing the direct session as active, but when I checked the sessions list earlier, it showed ended at 04:44 with a 24-second runtime, which means it must have completed right at that moment.\n\nNow looking at what's actually changed: the direct session has ended (it's gone from active to completed), the main session has disappeared entirely, and the group session has moved from idle to running. That's three notable changes, though none of them are critical failures—they're more like natural lifecycle transitions.\n\nActually, I need to reconsider what the cron job instructions are asking for. The directive says to stay silent if nothing has changed, but the threshold for \"changed\" isn't clearly defined. Should I treat these state transitions as significant enough to warrant a report, or are these normal operational changes that don't require notification?\n\nLooking at what's actually shifted: the Telegram session completed, the main session disappeared, and the group session started running. These feel like routine lifecycle events rather than actual failures or blockers. The pipeline itself remains healthy with no agents down and no blockers appearing. So strictly speaking, the core operational state hasn't changed—it's just session management happening as expected.\n\nBut the user did ask me to report whenever something changes, even if it's just a session dying. So I'll send a concise update acknowledging these transitions and confirming the pipeline is still operational.","thinkingSignature":"990ac05f2161308b5ea35f98e3d9a7d929aa71ae4730b9017a2fee85476ebbd9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_di3vmqukah8r_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/heartbeat-state.json","content":"{\n  \"updatedAt\": \"2026-04-15T04:47:00Z\",\n  \"activeSessions\": [\n    \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7\",\n    \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31\",\n    \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e\"\n  ],\n  \"idleSessions\": [],\n  \"completedSinceLast\": [\n    \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\",\n    \"agent:master-orchestrator:main\"\n  ],\n  \"disappearedSessions\": [\n    \"agent:master-orchestrator:main\"\n  ],\n  \"failedSessions\": [],\n  \"orphanedCrons\": [\n    \"cron:ac986a8d-2425-40c7-835b-ed9b101b0bff\",\n    \"cron:b653a6c0-143b-4b53-a242-034bc5fd9fca\"\n  ],\n  \"lastReportSent\": \"2026-04-15T04:47:00Z\",\n  \"lastReportGroup\": \"-5163901258\",\n  \"degradedReason\": null,\n  \"notes\": \"Lead direct session completed normally. Main session heartbeat ended. Group session activated. Pipeline HEALTHY.\"\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":427,"output":1295,"cacheRead":14272,"cacheWrite":6638,"totalTokens":22632,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776228443941,"responseId":"062e4b5c8e21f4c78f54d825d18608eb"}}
